subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Dorsum with extensive dark markings. Both male and female with dense black setae on all thoracic pleura. Male: fore femur slender, not modified (
Fig. 84
). Male genitalia moderate in size: tergum 8 with median notch on posterior margin; pygophore sub-ovate; proctiger elongate; paramere curved with distal part slightly broad and apex blunt (
Figs. 91–93
); endosoma as in 
Chen & Nieser (1993: 170)
. Female: sternum 7 large, not constricted laterally, posterior margin slightly produced (
Fig. 85
).
